lead_paragraph: The Liberty People at Buffalo disbanded on Thursday, after nominating Mr. GERRIT SMITH of New York, for President, and Mr. CHARLES DURKEE of Wisconsin, for Vice-President of the United States. Whether the twelve months' start thus secured for their candidates, is expected to be of service in the "long run," by equalizing the disparaty of numbers, and the like between them and the "great parties," is not understood. We presume such is the case.
abstract: Nominated for Vice Prest. by Buff. Conv.
